comments.body:
Unfortunately for some stupid reason I could not start CLC currently in "testing" , because of it not able to find the bootstrapper

{code}
[error:0631] Cannot find Eucalyptus bootstrapper: com/eucalyptus/bootstrap/SystemBootstrapper.
{code}

I don't know what the issue there was but everything seems to be working fine after reverting back to the last commit that was working for me.

Yes, I also tried clearing the class cache in /var/run/eucalyptus/classcache/ hoping it would get rebuild when I start the service.

Thanks [~mspaulding] for looking at the system, as you found out, the problem was with the old jars (including jibx 1.2.3) still hanging around at /usr/share/eucalyptus/ after clearing those out by simple doing a rm -rf /usr/share/eucalyptus/* and again running make install, it worked!

I had to explicitly specify the following in CLOUD_OPTS to make it use JAVA SDK 1.7 during runtime, everything is fine now.

{code}
CLOUD_OPTS="--java-home=/usr/lib/jvm/java-1.7.0-openjdk-1.7.0.9.x86_64"
{code}
